President of the Nigeria Football Federation, Amaju Pinnick has been removed as the 1st Vice President of the Confederation of African Football (CAF). Pinnick, who became CAF’s first vice president after the emergence of Madagascan, Ahmad Ahmad was removed at Thursday’s executive committee meeting after Congress was held. Sundiata Post has gathered that Omari Constant is CAF’s new 1st Vice President while football association of Morocco’s President, Fouzi Lekjaa is the 2nd Vice President. South African football aficionado, Danny Jordan has also been chosen as CAF’s 3rd Vice President after the Congress. Sundiata Post also gathered from sources that there is a new governing commission, to be headed by Ivorian lawyer, Kizito Michel Brizoua-Bi, who will be in charge of proceedings with CAF.